The paper deals with automated audio captioning using a neural network architecture, which falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP) and speech processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SD (Sound), which deals with audio and speech processing. The paper also uses an encoder-decoder scheme, which is commonly used in machine translation, and the resulting captions are evaluated using metrics utilized in machine translation and image captioning fields. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper uses recurrent neural networks (RNNs), which are a popular type of neural network for sequence modeling, and the proposed method is evaluated using data drawn from a commercial sound effects library. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
